THE University of the West of Scotland has been rated highly by students.A number of recent surveys - the Postgraduate Taught Experience Survey (PTES), the Postgraduate Research Experience Survey (PRES) and the National Survey of Student Engagement (NSSE) - gave students the chance to tell UWS about their experiences at the university.UWS was given positive ratings in all surveys and, in the National Survey of Student Engagement, 91% of students stated that they would recommend the university to a friend or relative.Professor Anne McGillivray, Dean of Students at UWS, said: &quot;Students are central to all that we do at UWS and I am delighted by the positive rankings we have received in these surveys.&quot;